<https://doi.org/10.5878/3fcc-7594> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/accessRights> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/access-right/PUBLIC>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/language> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/SWE>, <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/ENG>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher> <http://dataportal.se/organisation/SE2021002874>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Datamaterialet består av förekomst/icke förekomst av olika typer och orsaker av skador på träd i den svenska skogen, samt olika sorters av miljö- och beståndsvariabler. Variablerna är beskrivna på första sidan i Excel-bladet samt i filen \"Data description\"."@sv, "The data consist of presence/absence of different types and causes of damages on trees in the Swedish forest, as well as different types of environmental and stand variables. The variables are described on the first page of the Excel-file and in the file \"Data description\"."@en;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/spatial> <http://sws.geonames.org/2661886>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#contactPoint> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/e07bbdb258e12857cbfde7228f99cc27>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#distribution> <https://doi.org/10.5878/3fcc-7594#distribution>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/issued> "2024-06-27T13:22:03.745892Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#landingPage> <https://doi.org/10.5878/3fcc-7594>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/modified> "2024-06-27T13:22:03.745892Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "Data for Tree damage risk across gradients in tree species richness and stand age: implications for adaptive forest management"@sv, "Data för Risken för trädskador över gradienter i trädartrikedom och beståndsålder: betydelse för anpassat skogsbruk"@en;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/temporal> _:b0__8711.
_:b0__8711 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#endDate> "2017"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#startDate> "2003"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    a <http://purl.org/dc/terms/PeriodOfTime>
}

<feed> <https://w3id.org/tree#member> <#3f5afdbe93f56868589b0b06be1c6670>.
<#3f5afdbe93f56868589b0b06be1c6670> a <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#Update>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#object> <https://doi.org/10.5878/h2hc-h513>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#published> "2026-04-11T06:23:27.369Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>.
<#3f5afdbe93f56868589b0b06be1c6670> {
<https://doi.org/10.5878/h2hc-h513> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#keyword> "honungsbi"@sv, "honeybees"@en, "Varroa-motstånd"@sv, "Varroa Resistance"@en, "Uppfödning av esterferomoner"@sv, "Brood Ester Pheromones"@en, "Varroa destructor"@sv, "Varroa destructor"@en, "apis mellifera"@sv, "apis mellifera"@en, "odlingseffekter"@sv, "brood effects"@en, "varroa destructor"@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedAttribution> _:b0__1229.
_:b0__1229 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#hadRole> <http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/metadata-codelist/ResponsiblePartyRole/principalInvestigator>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#agent> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/8b0b6778073e11e6c8cce547878914e2>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Attribution>.
<https://doi.org/10.5878/h2hc-h513> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedAttribution> _:b0__8791.
_:b0__8791 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#hadRole> <http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/metadata-codelist/ResponsiblePartyRole/principalInvestigator>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#agent> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/1dcc58929506ad12a21aa4484a53abb9>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Attribution>.
<https://doi.org/10.5878/h2hc-h513> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/accessRights> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/access-right/PUBLIC>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/language> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/ENG>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher> <http://dataportal.se/organisation/SE2021002817>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Data om kemiska föreningar utvunna från honungsbiyngel (Apis mellifera) i en varroaresistent och varroamottaglig population. Prover togs 0, 6, 12, 18, 24 och 36 timmar efter avtäckning av yngel genom nedsänkning av puppor i pentan under 10 minuter. 6 bikupor från varje population användes och 3 replikat togs per bikupa per tidpunkt. FAME-kolonnen beräknades genom att tillsätta metylpalmitat, linoloat och stearat tillsammans, medan FAEE-kolumnen beräknades genom att tillsätta etylpalmitat, linoloat och stearat tillsammans. Prover analyserades med användning av gaskromatografi.\n\nR version 4.4.0 och RStudio version 1.4.1.748 användes för att analysera data. Alla paket och deras version listas i det bifogade R-skriptet.\n\nInkluderade datafiler:\nScaramella_et_al_2024_Contrast.tsv: 16 rader × 12 kolumner\nScaramella_et_al_2024_Data.tsv: 210 rader × 14 kolumner"@sv, "Data of chemical compounds extracted from honey bee (Apis mellifera) brood in a varroa resistant and varroa susceptible population. Samples were taken 0, 6, 12, 18, 24, and 36 hours after brood capping by immersing pupae in pentane for 10 minutes. 6 hives from each population were used, and 3 replicates were taken per hive per time point. The FAME column was calculated by adding Methyl Palmitate, Linoloate, and Stearate together, while the FAEE columb was calculateed by adding Ethyl Palmitate, Linoloate, and Stearate together. Samples were analyzed using gas chromatography. \n\nR version 4.4.0 and RStudio version 1.4.1.748 were used to analyze the data. All packages and their version is listed in the attached R script. \n\nData files included:\nScaramella_et_al_2024_Contrast.tsv: 16 rows × 12 columns\nScaramella_et_al_2024_Data.tsv: 210 rows × 14 columns"@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#contactPoint> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/51114b511532c3a2185d2769d45f9a7f>, <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/d12126b333905cfb3c2eb63a36194300>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#distribution> <https://doi.org/10.5878/h2hc-h513#distribution>;
