<feed> <https://w3id.org/tree#member> <#99cebd27381545bcc675f828d1f0c2cd>.
<#99cebd27381545bcc675f828d1f0c2cd> a <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#Update>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#object> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/f17dbf987960526901cc1918cde33dd3>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#published> "2026-04-11T06:23:30.252Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>.
<#99cebd27381545bcc675f828d1f0c2cd> {
<https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/f17dbf987960526901cc1918cde33dd3> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#keyword> "Linear B"@en, "linear B"@sv, "linear writing"@en, "linearskrift"@sv, "Linear A"@en, "linear A"@sv, "Ancient Greek language"@en, "klassisk grekiska"@sv, "Mycenaean culture"@en, "mykensk kultur"@sv, "Aegean culture"@en, "egeisk kultur"@sv, "Blegen, Carl (1887-1971)"@en, "Blegen, Carl (1887-1971)"@sv, "Chantraine, Heinrich (1929-2022)"@en, "Chantraine, Heinrich (1929-2022)"@sv, "Pallottino, Massimo (1909-1995)"@en, "Pallottino, Massimo (1909-1995)"@sv, "Furumark, Arne (1903-1982)"@en, "Furumark, Arne (1903-1982)"@sv, "Mycenaean Greek"@en, "mykensk grekiska"@sv, "Agia Triada"@en, "Hagia Triada"@sv, "Björck, Gudmund (1905-1955)"@en, "Björck, Gudmund (1905-1955)"@sv, "Knossos"@en, "Knossos"@sv, "Ventris, Michael (1922-1956)"@en, "Ventris, Michael (1922-1956)"@sv, "Palace of Nestor"@en, "Nestorspalatset"@sv, "Chadwick, John (1920-1998)"@en, "Chadwick, John (1920-1998)"@sv;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedAttribution> _:b0__42893.
_:b0__42893 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#hadRole> <http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/metadata-codelist/ResponsiblePartyRole/principalInvestigator>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#agent> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/4b26b56b4f031c3c874ff200d0597ca0>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Attribution>.
<https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/f17dbf987960526901cc1918cde33dd3> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/accessRights> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/access-right/PUBLIC>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/language> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/SWE>, <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/ENG>, <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/DEU>, <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/FRA>, <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/ITA>, <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/GMY>, <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/GRC>, <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/LAB>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher> <http://dataportal.se/organisation/SE2021002932>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "The Swedish professor of Classical archaeology Arne Furumark (1903–1982), spent most of his active career studying the Minoan and the Mycenean cultures on ancient Crete. Besides his archaeological work he was also interested in Linear A, the Minoan syllabic script. The digitized letter collection comprises Furumark’s collected letters från the 1950s, the era when the decipherment of Linear B was completed, and contains letters from several important 20th century philologists, such as John Chadwick (Cambridge), Massimo Pallottino (Rom), och Heinrich Chantraine (Mannheim). Furumark also had a habit of keeping copies of his own letters.\n\nThe letters have been photo scanned and have been sorted with information about sender, recipient, location, date, and language (Swedish, English, German, French, Italian, Russian). Most of the letters have also been transcribed, with Linear A and Linear B signs inserted in unicode."@en, "Den svenske arkeologen Arne Furumark (1903–1982), professor i Uppsala (1952–1970), studerade bland annat den minoiska och den mykenska kulturen på Kreta. Förutom sitt arbete som arkeolog var han också mycket intresserad av Linear A, den fornkretensiska stavelseskriften. Furumarks samlade kvarvarande brev från 1950-talet, då tolkningen av Linear B slutfördes, innehåller brev från en rad framstående 1900-talsfilologer, bland annat John Chadwick (Cambridge), Massimo Pallottino (Rom), och Heinrich Chantraine (Mannheim). I samlingen finns oftast även kopior av de brev Furumark själv skrev.\n\nBreven har fotoscannats och har taggats med information om avsändare, mottagare, ort, datum, och språk (svenska, engelska, tyska, franska, italienska, ryska). Majoriteten av brev har också transkriberats, och skrivtecken på linear A och linear B har då infogats i unicode."@sv;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/issued> "2025-06-02T13:56:27.043918Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/modified> "2025-08-12T07:10:50.932416Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "Arne Furumark's correspondence"@en, "Arne Furumarks korrespondens"@sv;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#theme> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/data-theme/EDUC>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/temporal> _:b0__75589.
_:b0__75589 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#endDate> "1958"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#startDate> "1951"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    a <http://purl.org/dc/terms/PeriodOfTime>.
